physics_precondition [{'condition': 'Re_H sits in the post-transition regime where Xr/H is weakly Re-sensitive (7600 adapter vs 5100 reference, drift absorbed by 10% tolerance)', 'satisfied_by_current_adapter': 'partial', 'evidence_ref': 'src/foam_agent_adapter.py:1178-1184 — nu=1/Re=1/7600 with U_bulk=1. Regime argument documented in yaml header lines 6-13; accepted under Gate Q-4 Path A. The regime match is qualitative-plateau, not a 2% quantified tolerance.'}, {'condition': 'Turbulence model adequate for transitional/turbulent separated flow (adapter uses RANS k-omega SST against a DNS reference)', 'satisfied_by_current_adapter': True, 'evidence_ref': "DEC-V61-052 round 2c: default RAS model is now kOmegaSST (selected via TaskSpec.boundary_conditions.turbulence_model, default 'kOmegaSST'). SST's F1/F2 blending — k-ω near the wall, k-ε in the free stream — captures the separated shear layer substantially better than standard k-ε on BFS. Measured improvement on the same mesh: kEpsilon → Xr/H=3.99 (-36.3% miss), kOmegaSST + x-graded mesh → Xr/H=5.64 (-9.9% miss, inside 10% tolerance). kEpsilon remains available as a wrong_model diagnostic."}, {'condition': 'Mesh resolves reattachment region + shear layer at declared 36000 cells', 'satisfied_by_current_adapter': 'partial', 'evidence_ref': "DEC-V61-052 adapter: 3-block topology produces 7360 cells (ncx_A=40, ncy_A=16, ncx_B=120, ncy_B1=40, ncy_B2=16) on the quick-run fixture. B1 near-floor dy=0.025 gives first-cell y+≈5 (Spalding blending wall function handles it) and recirculation bubble spans ~16 cells laterally, ~40 vertically. G3/G4/G5 gate battery now all clean. YAML's 36000-cell aspiration stands for the authoritative mesh; the 7360-cell fixture is a known-undersampled-but-stable quick-run. Mesh independence study deferred to a follow-up DEC."}, {'condition': 'Residual convergence reaches attestor A4/A5/A6 thresholds', 'satisfied_by_current_adapter': True, 'evidence_ref': 'DEC-V61-052 Batch B + round 2d: 1500-iter simpleFoam run under bounded-upwind + SIMPLEC + Spalding wall fn + kOmegaSST. Residual plateau: Ux 6.42e-6 → 6.41e-6 across t=1400→1500 (+0.1% per 100 iters). Uy 1.10e-4, continuity sum_local=1.30e-7, sum_global=~1e-9. Two-fixture Xr stability: t=1000 fixture → 5.642, t=1500 fixture → 5.647 (+0.09% drift over 500 iters). G3/G4/G5 gate battery all clean. Supersedes the pre-DEC-V61-052 ATTEST_HAZARD caused by the single-block generator diverging k/ε to 1e+30.'}]
contract_status SATISFIED — DEC-V61-052 closed all four defects V61-051 exposed (flat channel with no step; k/ε to 1e+30; misaligned Xr probe; no wall-shear measurement). The rewritten 3-block mesh produces a real BFS field (15154 pts, 0 points in step void, |U|_max=1.04·U_bulk). Round 3 (Codex r2 #1) landed the authoritative wall-shear Xr extractor: read `lower_wall` face tau_x from the allPatches VTK, find the pos→neg sign change (OpenFOAM's convention for -tau_xy on a floor where reversed flow → positive), interpolate to the zero crossing. Current fixture yields Xr/H = 5.647 via `reattachment_method: wall_shear_tau_x_zero_crossing`. Round 2a near-wall Ux proxy (Xr/H=5.647 via `near_wall_tau_x_proxy_via_Ux`) remains as a cross-check and agrees to the 4th digit. Round 2c flipped the default RAS model from kEpsilon (Xr/H=3.99, -36.3% miss) to kOmegaSST + x-graded mesh (simpleGrading 0.25 near the step corner), bringing Xr/H to 5.647 — -9.8% vs Driver 1985 = 6.26, INSIDE the 10% tolerance band. Round 2d raised endTime to 1500 and demonstrated two-fixture Xr stability across t=1000/1500 (drift +0.09%) + Ux residual plateau at t=1400→1500 (+0.1% per 100 iters). Round 2b added a structured preflight scalar-contract gate that cannot be evaded by status renaming. Solver: simpleFoam, kOmegaSST + SIMPLEC + bounded-linearUpwind + Spalding wall function, final continuity sum_local=1.30e-7 on 7360 cells. kEpsilon remains available as a `wrong_model` diagnostic via boundary_conditions.turbulence_model override. Geometry, solver convergence, and headline scalar all pass.

