FINDINGS:
  #1 [MED] The new `allPatches` mask does not strictly isolate the downstream `lower_wall`.
      `[src/foam_agent_adapter.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/src/foam_agent_adapter.py:7802)` uses `y<0.05 && x>0.05`. In this 3-block topology that matches the downstream floor at `[src/foam_agent_adapter.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/src/foam_agent_adapter.py:7044)`, but it also matches the low-`y` B1 outlet face at `[src/foam_agent_adapter.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/src/foam_agent_adapter.py:7033)`. I verified on the staged `allPatches_1500.vtk` that the mask contains 120 `lower_wall` cells plus 2 outlet cells at `(30, 0.0125)` and `(30, 0.0375)`. The first POS→NEG crossing is still the correct `x≈5.647`, so this is not a scalar blocker, but `reattachment_n_floor_pts=122` and the “122 downstream-floor face centres on lower_wall” wording are not literally true.

  #2 [MED] Batch D’s BFS figure still computes `Xr` from the near-wall `Ux` proxy while the frontend copy says wall-shear.
      `[scripts/flow-field-gen/generate_contours.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/scripts/flow-field-gen/generate_contours.py:486)` re-probes `Xr` with the Path-2 band-averaged `Ux` zero crossing, and `[scripts/flow-field-gen/generate_contours.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/scripts/flow-field-gen/generate_contours.py:561)` saves provenance saying `near-wall Ux sign-change`. But `[flowFields.ts](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/ui/frontend/src/data/flowFields.ts:107)` and `[flowFields.ts](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/ui/frontend/src/data/flowFields.ts:108)` tell the user that the same figure’s `Xr/H=5.65` came from `wallShearStress` on `lower_wall`. On the current fixture the two methods agree within about `0.004%`, so the number is coherent, but the method attribution is stronger than the artifact chain supports.

  #3 [LOW] The new diagnostic flags exist in executor `key_quantities`, but the serialized audit surface still collapses them.
      `[audit_real_run_measurement.yaml](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/ui/backend/tests/fixtures/runs/backward_facing_step/audit_real_run_measurement.yaml:20)` stores only `value`, `quantity`, and `extraction_source: key_quantities_direct`, not `reattachment_method` or the new wall-shear/proxy flags. Then `[comparison_report.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/ui/backend/services/comparison_report.py:578)` maps the Compare-tab method to that generic `extraction_source`, so the card cannot distinguish authoritative wall-shear success from proxy fallback without opening raw `key_quantities`. This does not create stale data on BFS, but round-2 finding #3 is only fully solved inside the extractor, not in the persisted review surface.

SUMMARY:
  The round-2 HIGH finding is closed in substance: Path-1a now owns the scalar, returns before Path-2, and I re-ran `python3.11 scripts/preflight_case_visual.py backward_facing_step` successfully on the current tree with `reattachment_length=5.647` vs `6.26` (`-9.8%`). The BFS Compare-tab branch is correctly scoped, no non-BFS case will accidentally pick up the Xr card, and no Path-2 diagnostic flag can make that card show stale data because the card never reads those flags. The gold YAML’s residual/stationarity/continuity wording now matches the cited artifacts, and `solver_output` is still the right `kind` for `velocity_streamlines.png`. I do not see an accessibility or i18n blocker in the PASS/FAIL card.

  DEC-V61-052 is ready to close with comments; I do not see any remaining HIGH issue that warrants a round 4. If you want a small cleanup pass after closure, the highest-value hardening is to tighten the wall mask so the outlet cannot leak in, align the BFS figure/caption with the actual measurement method (or switch the generator to wall-shear), and optionally replace `sorted(cand)[-1]` with numeric timestep parsing plus a wall-shear vs `Ux` sanity check.
